    <note>Li(2) Hong(2) [1038] His ancestors descended from the Tang Xiping Wang, Longxi Li(2) Sheng [3529]. Sheng's grandson, You [4172], moved from Jingzhao, Changan xian to Yuanzhou, Yichun xian. His son, Xianyong [4173], retired to Jizhou, Lushan to compose poetry. Hong(2)'s great great grandfather and Sheng's 6th generation descendant, Li(2) Hanzhang [1025], first moved to Xuanzhou when he was appointed prefect and remained there permanently. Hong(2) was called a Xuancheng aristocrat (shidafu). His son-in-law, Weng(1) Shengzhi [4032], had the same generational name as Weng(1) Yanguo's [1956] grandsons and grandnephews. His grandson-in-law, Lu(9) Dezhong [3658], was Lu(9) Guangwen's [1313] son. Anhui TZ, 154.14a; Zhang Kuo, WJ, 8.3a; Han Yuanji, WJ, 20.6a-10b; SHY:ZG, 70.47a. CBD, 2, 831.</note>
